Language name: KONYAGI
Language number: 4145
Alternate names: Basari
Classification: Niger-Kordofanian, West Atlantic
Comments: Konyagi has two level tones and contours derived 
from their combination. 'Schwa' and 'ash' are weak vowels 
after which consonants are lengthened; the remaining 
vowels may appear long under predictable conditions.
Sources: 

Santos, R. 1977. Phonologie et Morphotonologie de la 
Langue W~ey~ (Konyagi). Les Langues Africaines au Senegal 
no. 69. Centre de Linguistique Appliquee de Dakar.